Program: Discovery
Title: Anthropology - the early anthropologist
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jry20
Last Broadcast Date: 21 March 2002
Second in a series examining the discipline of social anthropology. The programme examines why anthropology is like no other discipline, in that its relationship between the researcher and the researched brings with it many rights and responsibilities. Presenter: Anna Buckley.